Anglo American Plc (AAL)  has been named as
the preferred bidder for a 59 percent stake in Mozambican coal
mining firm Minas de Revuboe, which is currently owned by
Australia-based Talbot Group Investments Pty Ltd., the Sunday
Times reported, without saying where it got the information.  A spokeswoman for Anglo American wasnâ€™t immediately
